erline;">wrote about Primer in April 2022</a><span>, they were a mostly onl=
ine home for ambitious kids to learn in Clubs with other ambitious kids out=
side of school that was just getting ready to launch its first Microschools=
=2E They have since gone all-in on in-p=
erson Microschools based on the realiz=
ation that if you want to actually fix K-12 education, you can&#8217;t nibb=
le around the edges with software; you have to build a better version of th=
e system and compete.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(5=
4,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Primer is running the </=
span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/b6c421d0-cf34-4344-8410-c5317=
