>One vertically integrated startup willing to compete with incumbents to fi=
x the actual problem is worth 1,000 startups writing software to improve th=
is or that little problem on the margin.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">If you wa=
nt to fix energy, you need to build lots of nuclear reactors and install lo=
ts of batteries.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);lin=
e-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">If you want to fix space exploration, you =
need to build your own rockets.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rg=
