ou want to fix K-12 education, you need to build schools.</strong></p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size:=
 16px;">For two school years, that&#8217;s what Primer has been doing.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-s=
ize: 16px;">Primer partners with teachers in local communities and gives th=
em the tools they need to start their own schools. They help them find a sp=
ace &#8211; a church, a community center, any space that isn&#8217;t in use=
